The paper focuses on developing a recommendation system for groups of mobile users based on their location traces and social context. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves developing a prediction model and integrating it with a recommendation API, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the user experience and usability of the system, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves analyzing a real-world dataset, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
